MMLLPP_LLIIFFEE -- Environmental Variable

Set default life for print jobs

When the command  llpp spools a job for printing,  it reads the environmental
variable MMLLPP_LLIIFFEE  to set the job's ``life  expectancy''.  MMLLPP_LLIIFFEE must be
one of the following:

TT  Temporary: live in the queue for two hours.

SS  Short-term: live in the queue for 48 hours.

LL  Long-term: live in the queue for 72 hours.

The default life expectancy is SS.

To  change  the   default  values  for  life-expectancies,  edit  the  file
/uussrr/ssppooooll/mmllpp/ccoonnttrrooll. For details, see the Lexicon article ccoonnttrroollss.

